question: What is seqkit?
answer: SeqKit is a cross-platform ultrafast comprehensive toolkit for FASTA/Q processing. It provides executable binary files for all major operating systems, including Windows, Linux, and Mac OS X, and can be directly used without any dependencies or pre-configurations. It demonstrates competitive performance in execution time and memory usage compared to similar tools, enabling researchers to rapidly accomplish common FASTA/Q file manipulations.

question: What is spectra?
answer: SpectrA stands for Sparse Eigenvalue Computation Toolkit as a Redesigned ARPACK. It is a C++ library for large scale eigenvalue problems, built on top of Eigen, an open source linear algebra library. SpectrA is implemented as a header-only C++ library, whose only dependency, Eigen, is also header-only. Hence SpectrA can be easily embedded in C++ projects that require calculating eigenvalues of large matrices.
